      "span_text": "In mice, genetic maoa ablation increases brain tissue concentrations of 5-HT, NE and DA during development and early adulthood.  The most prominent teratogenic consequence of murine maoa ablation, the disruption of barrel fields in the somatosensory cortex, has been linked to increased 5-HT signaling during perinatal development."
